{
  "text": "Numerous studies reported using computers with persons having poor vision or lower levels of literacy or when eliciting answers to sensitive issues. To meet the diverse needs of patients, one computer technology design included an audio computer-assisted, self-interviewing (ACASI) format. [CITATION_1] 30 With ACASI, the questionnaire is programmed on a computer to be displayed on the screen. Each question is voice recorded along with accompanying instructions to navigate the computer screens. The respondent hears the questions as they are visually displayed on the screen and then answers the question by touching the computer screen. Answering questions via touch screen does not require keyboard skills, allowing persons to answer questions without difficulty. 30 Results from ACASI are then immediately available to the professional as part of the health-screening assessment.",
  "citation_candidates": [
